---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Support — Nostaliga"
  description="Getting help with Nostaliga: contact, FAQs, and how to reset the app."
  path="/support"
>
  <article class="pt-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">
      Support
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      The fastest way to get help is email. Include your iOS version, the
      integration you were using, and a short description of what happened.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-[color:var(--color-bg-soft)] p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">Email</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
        <a href="mailto:dinakar@pageloop.ai?subject=Nostaliga%20support"
          >dinakar@pageloop.ai</a
        >
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
        Usual response time: within 2 business days.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">
      Frequently asked
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-8 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          How do I connect Spotify / Last.fm / Trakt / Swarm / Strava / Lightroom?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Open Settings → Integrations, tap the service, and follow the OAuth
          flow. You'll be redirected back to Nostaliga once you authorize. A
          green check appears next to the service when connection is complete.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          I connected a service but nothing is showing up.
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Pull to refresh on the main timeline. Background sync also runs
          periodically — open the app once and give it a few minutes on the
          first connection for an initial import.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Background sync isn't running.
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          iOS controls the schedule — background tasks run when the system
          decides it's a good time (battery, network, usage patterns).
          Keeping Background App Refresh on for Nostaliga in
          <em>iOS Settings → General → Background App Refresh</em> increases
          how often it runs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          How do I reset the app?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Settings → Privacy → Delete All Data. This removes the on-device
          database, every OAuth token, every cached file, and every
          preference. Use this before uninstalling if you want a clean slate.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Does my data leave the device?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Only when you explicitly ask Nostaliga to fetch history from a
          third-party service you connected — those requests go directly to
          that service. Matching, correlation, and rendering all happen
          locally. See the
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for the complete breakdown.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Does Nostaliga work on iPad and Mac?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Yes — iPhone, iPad, and Mac (Apple Silicon). visionOS support is in
          progress. HealthKit timelines are iPhone-only because HealthKit
          itself is iPhone-only.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          I want to delete my Nostaliga account.
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          There is no Nostaliga account to delete — Nostaliga has no server
          and stores nothing about you. To remove every piece of local data,
          tap Settings → Privacy → Delete All Data, then uninstall the app.
          To cut off Nostaliga's access to a third-party service from that
          service's side, visit the connected-apps settings on their site
          (Spotify Apps, Strava My Apps, etc.) and revoke Nostaliga.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Reporting a bug or requesting a feature.
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Email works best — describe what you did, what you expected, and
          what happened. Screenshots help. A short screen recording is even
          better. See the email address above.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
